          <p>This does cause the thumb to appear at the top of the scrollbar, however, the scrolling is inverted(the top of the scrollbar shows the bottom of the content)</p>
<p>To fix this, change the functions so they look like this:<br />
<div class="geshifilter"><div class="javascript geshifilter-javascript" style="font-family:monospace;">$<span style="color: #000000;">&#40;</span><span style="color: #ff0000;">&quot;#artist_bio_slider&quot;</span><span style="color: #000000;">&#41;</span>.<span style="color: #000000;">slider</span><span style="color: #000000;">&#40;</span><span style="color: #000000;">&#123;</span><br />
